---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Canada Trip" description="About this FOSSY 2026 Vancouver trip planner.">
  <Nav />
  <main>
    <div class="about-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="section-label">About This Site</p>
        <h1>FOSSY 2026 Vancouver</h1>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-grid">
        <section class="card about-card">
          <h2>The Trip</h2>
          <p>A solo drive from Seattle to Vancouver, BC for <a href="https://fossy.us" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FOSSY</a> — the Free and Open Source Software Yearly conference.</p>
          <ul class="about-list">
            <li>🚗 Driving SEA → Vancouver (~225 km, pickup truck)</li>
            <li>📅 August 6–9, 2026 (4 days)</li>
            <li>🐧 FOSSY: all 4 days at UBC Campus</li>
            <li>🤠 Solo traveler</li>
            <li>🍦 Ice cream selfie tradition (4 spots planned)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card about-card">
          <h2>The Site</h2>
          <p>A personal trip planner built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>, hosted on <a href="https://pages.github.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Pages</a>. Part of a monorepo at <a href="/">sfalken.github.io</a>.</p>
          <ul class="about-list">
            <li>💵 Multi-currency: USD + CAD with live exchange rate toggle</li>
            <li>🗺️ Interactive maps (Leaflet + OpenStreetMap)</li>
            <li>✅ Planning checklist with browser persistence</li>
            <li>📱 Progressive Web App — installable, offline-capable</li>
            <li>🔒 Optional PII encryption for booking details</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="card about-card">
          <h2>FOSSY</h2>
          <p>FOSSY (Free and Open Source Software Yearly) is the annual community-organized conference celebrating Linux, open source software, and the communities behind them. It covers topics from kernel development to community building. The 2026 edition is held on the <strong>University of British Columbia (UBC) campus</strong> in Point Grey, Vancouver.</p>
          <a href="https://fossy.us" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:1rem;align-self:flex-start;">Visit fossy.us →</a>
        </section>

        <section class="card about-card">
          <h2>Vancouver, BC</h2>
          <p>Vancouver is one of the most livable cities in the world — a spectacular mix of mountains, ocean, rainforest, and cosmopolitan culture. August is Vancouver's driest and sunniest month. UBC campus is 10 km west of downtown in Point Grey, easily reached via the 99 B-Line bus.</p>
          <ul class="about-list">
            <li>🌆 Population: ~680,000 (metro ~2.8M)</li>
            <li>🌡️ August: 18–25°C (64–77°F), Vancouver's driest month</li>
            <li>🕐 Timezone: Pacific (same as Seattle)</li>
            <li>🛂 Entry: US passport required. No visa needed for US citizens.</li>
            <li>💵 Currency: Canadian dollar (CAD)</li>
            <li>🚌 Transit to UBC: 99 B-Line from downtown (~30 min)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-hero { background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--ca-red) 0%, var(--ca-red-dark) 100%); color: white; padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem; }
  .about-hero .section-label { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); }
  .about-hero h1 { color: white; }
  .about-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .about-card { padding: 1.5rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .about-card h2 { font-size: 1.15rem; color: var(--ca-red); }
  .about-card p { font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.6; }
  .about-list { list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--gray-700); }
</style>
